text: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve, or BTNR, is on Bukit Timah Hill. It is the largest primary forest in Singapore. Singaporeâ€™s original tropical primary rainforest ecosystem is half of the reserve. At the top of the hill, there is a rock showing the height, latitude and longtitude. == ASEAN Heritage Park status == BTNR is the second ASEAN Heritage Park in Singapore, after Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve. BTNR became a Heritage Park on 18 October 2011. == References == Category:Geography of Singapore Category:Parks in Asia
